  "text": "Thus, the aim of this paper is to reduce the errors of such derivative estimators. For this, Section 2 allows κ, μ to be real: since the use of (7) induces some natural limitations (κ, μ, ∈ N) we use truncated Jacobi orthogonal series to obtain a natural extension of (4). Let us recall that, in [CITATION_1] , such truncated Jacobi orthogonal series were shown to be related to (7) and the obtained estimators [CITATION_2] . Such obtained estimators are thus called minimal Jacobi estimators and are clearly rooted from [CITATION_3] .",
